"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-showbiz-tv-radio-1931541-richard-madeley-blast-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  TheParis Olympicsopening ceremony sparked controversy last week when it unintentionally featureda parody of Leonardo da Vinci's The Last Supperstarring drag queens and dancers lining a large table.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 110, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.002272461536837e-17, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While artistic director Thomas Jolly has said da Vinci's 15th-century painting was not his inspiration for the act, some have accused it of mocking the biblical scene.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9830602969673492, \"rank\": 0.017024114150512325, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Catholic Church said it \\\"included scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity.\\\"\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 374, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 381, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999996905242393, \"rank\": 3.077896261307322e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 449, \"end\": 461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9996292385818232, \"rank\": 0.00037068691108289967, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Archbishop Charles Scicluna, the highest-ranking Catholic official in Malta, contacted France's ambassador to Malta to express his \\\"distress and great disappointment at the insult\\\".\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9981478621886334, \"rank\": 0.001851508757630014, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 480, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Scicluna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\"}, {\"begin\": 518, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999917408786, \"rank\": 5.809141692408278e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9998488511655257, \"rank\": 0.0001511419818497508, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}, {\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8588577273254817, \"rank\": 0.15985549258522244, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9998488511655257, \"rank\": 0.0001511419818497508, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richard Madeleyhas now joined the backlash, saying the act was \\\"insulting to Christians\\\" and questioning whether another religion would have been \\\"mocked\\\" in the same way.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7670368988148364, \"rank\": 0.3003460742840986, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Was Imane Khelif born male or female?\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All the facts over athlete in Olympics row    We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  TheGood Morning Britainpresenter, 68, wrote in his new column for the Daily Express: \\\"I am not a Christian; sadly I do not believe in God (sadly, because I realise it would be a great comfort) but nevertheless I was offended by the drag queen parody of Leonardo da Vinci's The Last Supper during the Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3662946602743553e-17, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}, {\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.979680903284217, \"rank\": 0.02074052535365265, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1416, \"end\": 1433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.002272461536837e-17, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was just rude.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not mean the drag queens themselves - drag is so mainstream now, it's boring - but why gratuitously insult millions of watching Christians who up to that moment were enjoying the ceremony?\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7670368988148364, \"rank\": 0.3003460742840986, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Mocking Christians is easy.\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1714, \"end\": 1724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7670368988148364, \"rank\": 0.3003460742840986, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They do not punch back.\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So there was nothing brave about the parody.\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But mocking another religion?\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Islam, say?\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They would not dare.\\\"\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the days following the opening ceremony, Paris 2024 organisersissued an apology to those who were offended.\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1914, \"end\": 1924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999813781, \"rank\": 1.8625038072890545e-10, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spokesperson Anne Descamps told a press conference on Sunday: \\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[The opening ceremony] tried to celebrate community tolerance.\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We believe this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offence we are really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director behind the opening ceremony, said he did not intend \\\"to be subversive\\\", \\\"mock\\\" or \\\"shock\\\".\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9830602969673492, \"rank\": 0.017024114150512325, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"We wanted to talk about diversity.\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Diversity means being together.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted to include everyone, as simple as that.\\\"\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He added that he had intended for it to depict a pagan feast linked to the gods of Olympus.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2591, \"end\": 2596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.9999900086082847, \"rank\": 9.105529756386592e-06, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}, {\"begin\": 2625, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9999549266200781, \"rank\": 4.494130728987746e-05, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2772, \"end\": 2785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3662946602743553e-17, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2821, \"end\": 2834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3662946602743553e-17, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"